Session of 2025
SENATE BILL No. 222
By Committee on Judiciary
2-5
1 AN ACT concerning state agencies; relating to interpretation of statutes,
2 rules and regulations and documents with the force and effect of law;
3 prohibiting deference to the agency's interpretation by a state court or
4 an officer hearing an administrative action.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. (a) In interpreting a state statute, rule and regulation or
8 document that has the force and effect of law, a state court or an officer
9 hearing an administrative action may consider but shall not defer to a state
10 agency's interpretation of such statute, rule and regulation or document and
11 shall interpret the meaning and effect of such statute, rule and regulation or
12 document de novo.
13 (b) In an action brought by or against a state agency, after applying all
14 customary tools of interpretation and rules of statutory construction
15 pursuant to law, a state court or an officer hearing an administrative action
16 shall exercise any remaining doubt in favor of a reasonable interpretation
17 that limits the state agency's powers and maximizes individual liberty.
18 (c) As used in this section, "rule and regulation" and "state agency"
19 mean the same as defined in K.S.A. 77-602, and amendments thereto.
20 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
21 publication in the statute book.

